Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new hierarchical planning framework for robotic motion planning in architectural construction.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper may involve computer vision techniques for perception and recognition of architectural structures.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is another possible category as the paper may involve 3D modeling and visualization of architectural structures.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper involves computational methods for solving the assembly planning problem.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve multimedia techniques for visualization and simulation of the assembly process.
